@* Markup only — all logic lives in CanvasTextOverlay.razor.cs. The input starts hidden
   (display:none inline, so there is no flash before the module attaches) and absolutely
   positioned — the consumer must place this component inside the same position:relative
   container as the canvas. Visual styling (colors, border, font) comes from Class; the inline
   style carries only the mechanics. All events are wired JS-side in webgl-text-overlay.js
   (selective preventDefault + synchronous selection reads need raw DOM listeners). *@
<input @ref="_inputRef"
       type="text"
       class="@Class"
       spellcheck="false"
       autocomplete="off"
       autocapitalize="off"
       enterkeyhint="search"
       style="position:absolute;display:none;box-sizing:border-box;z-index:10;" />
